n the “skin” of the figurines are thought to be representations of fertility. It seems common world-wide for women (or statues of women) to be marked on belly, breasts and pubic area.\r\n\r\nWe have written records from Asia that are very ancient and as early as 3oo BCE there are mentions of tattoos and their symbolic meanings. It is clear that in Asia, as in other parts of the world, tattoos were not just for decoration but for punishment–criminals were often permanently marked.\"'),(7785,47,2,38,0,'<kml xmlns=\"http://earth.google.com/kml/2.0\"><Folder><name>OpenLayers export</name><description>Exported on Tue Nov 27 2012 19:22:55 GMT-0800 (PST)</description><Placemark><name>OpenLayers.Feature.Vector_160</name><description>No description available</description><Point><coordinates>15384554.584165,4429218.0224192</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>OpenLayers.Feature.Vector_165</name><description>No description available</description><Point><coordinates>12018879.35518,3881317.4037474</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder></kml>|1|1217410.0156495|2628973.1324972|ghyb\r\nAsia'),(7783,47,2,40,0,'2007'),(7784,47,2,51,0,'Website'),(7781,47,2,39,0,'Unknown'),(7782,47,2,48,0,'http://tattoo.infmom.net/history/tattoo-history-in-asia/'),(7778,47,2,50,0,'\"Tattoo history in Asia\"'),(7711,41,2,51,0,'Website'),(7095,32,2,38,0,'<kml xmlns=\"http://earth.google.com/kml/2.0\"><Folder><name>OpenLayers export</name><description>Exported on Mon Nov 19 2012 13:46:24 GMT-0800 (PST)</description><Placemark><name>OpenLayers.Feature.Vector_145</name><description>No description available</description><Point><coordinates>15462466.980391,4586671.5093032</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder></kml>|1|-661465.51195274|2708155.1024279|ghyb\r\nAsia'),(2583,29,3,74,0,'8'),(2584,29,3,75,0,'3'),(2585,29,3,77,0,'a:9:{s:8:\"FileName\";s:36:\"7891a3475085814ab8dcf7ee8f75148c.jpg\";s:12:\"FileDateTime\";i:1352317815;s:8:\"FileSize\";i:108222;s:8:\"FileType\";i:2;s:8:\"MimeType\";s