ced cuts into which a dark pigment such as lampblack or charcoal is inserted. Kolo cuts are made with a special Y-shaped blade, one of which can be seen in the ‘Body Arts’ display in the Museum.\"'),(11961,62,2,48,0,'Pitt Rivers Museum'),(11958,62,2,49,0,'Africa, 20th century, cultural'),(7978,35,2,49,0,'Africa, 20th century, historical'),(6540,34,2,44,0,'English'),(4639,72,3,74,0,'8'),(4640,72,3,75,0,'3'),(4641,72,3,77,0,'a:17:{s:8:\"FileName\";s:36:\"309b7df7e11dda726fb15c2fd007e477.jpg\";s:12:\"FileDateTime\";i:1352584321;s:8:\"FileSize\";i:52166;s:8:\"FileType\";i:2;s:8:\"MimeType\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";s:13:\"SectionsFound\";s:33:\"ANY_TAG, IFD0, THUMBNAIL, COMMENT\";s:8:\"COMPUTED\";a:7:{s:4:\"html\";s:24:\"width=\"248\" height=\"318\"\";s:6:\"Height\";i:318;s:5:\"Width\";i:248;s:7:\"IsColor\";i:1;s:17:\"ByteOrderMotorola\";i:1;s:18:\"Thumbnail.FileType\";i:2;s:18:\"Thumbnail.MimeType\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:11:\"Orientation\";i:1;s:11:\"XResolution\";s:13:\"4718592/65536\";s:11:\"YResolution\";s:13:\"4718592/65536\";s:14:\"ResolutionUnit\";i:2;s:8:\"Software\";s:15:\"QuickTime 7.7.1\";s:8:\"DateTime\";s:19:\"2012:11:10 12:49:03\";s:12:\"HostComputer\";s:15:\"Mac OS X 10.7.4\";s:16:\"YCbCrPositioning\";i:1;s:9:\"THUMBNAIL\";a:7:{s:11:\"Compression\";i:6;s:11:\"XResolution\";s:13:\"4718592/65536\";s:11:\"YResolution\";s:13:\"4718592/65536\";s:14:\"ResolutionUnit\";i:2;s:21:\"JPEGInterchangeFormat\";i:296;s:27:\"JPEGInterchangeFormatLength\";i:5681;s:16:\"YCbCrPositioning\";i:1;}s:7:\"COMMENT\";a:1:{i:0;s:10:\"AppleMark\n\";}}'),(6228,100,2,46,0,'Unknown'),(6229,100,2,42,0,'JPEG'),(6230,100,2,51,0,'Image'),(6231,100,2,43,0,'Unknown'),(6232,100,2,38,0,'<kml xmlns=\"http://earth.google.com/kml/2.0\"><Folder><name>OpenLayers export</name><description>Exported on Sat Nov 10 2012 15:40:08 GMT-0800 (PST)</description><Placemark><name>OpenLayers.Feature.Vector_160</name><description>No description available</description><Point><coordinates>267785.98154172,1202251.61919