oftware\";s:15:\"QuickTime 7.7.1\";s:8:\"DateTime\";s:19:\"2012:11:10 12:49:41\";s:12:\"HostComputer\";s:15:\"Mac OS X 10.7.4\";s:16:\"YCbCrPositioning\";i:1;s:9:\"THUMBNAIL\";a:7:{s:11:\"Compression\";i:6;s:11:\"XResolution\";s:13:\"4718592/65536\";s:11:\"YResolution\";s:13:\"4718592/65536\";s:14:\"ResolutionUnit\";i:2;s:21:\"JPEGInterchangeFormat\";i:296;s:27:\"JPEGInterchangeFormatLength\";i:5564;s:16:\"YCbCrPositioning\";i:1;}s:7:\"COMMENT\";a:1:{i:0;s:10:\"AppleMark\n\";}}'),(9470,87,2,49,0,'Benin, 21st Century, methodological'),(9471,87,2,41,0,'\"First, the scar pattern is divined with cowrie shells cast into a water pot. Next, the child is placed on a bed of leaves and then the cutting begins on the temple. Every child I witnessed being cut screamed and writhed in pain. One passed out halfway through the cutting, but he regained consciousness towards the end and resumed his bloodcurdling cries. Finally, once the shea butter is applied to the wounds for healing, every child seemingly fell fast asleep which was a calming sight. I can only imagine how my body would react to such a surge of physical and emotional shock especially at such a young age!\"'),(9472,87,2,39,0,'Lars Krutak'),(9473,87,2,48,0,'Lars Krutak'),(9474,87,2,45,0,'http://www.larskrutak.com/'),(9475,87,2,40,0,'2002'),(9476,87,2,47,0,'Lars Krutak'),(9477,87,2,46,0,'Unknown'),(9478,87,2,42,0,'JPEG'),(9479,87,2,51,0,'Image'),(9480,87,2,43,0,'Unknown'),(9481,87,2,38,0,'<kml xmlns=\"http://earth.google.com/kml/2.0\"><Folder><name>OpenLayers export</name><description>Exported on Sat Nov 10 2012 15:18:19 GMT-0800 (PST)</description><Placemark><name>OpenLayers.Feature.Vector_160</name><description>No description available</description><Point><coordinates>282461.89097039,1207143.5890077</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder></kml>|5|390085.22678094|815786.00424203|ghyb\r\nAfrica'),(4173,57,3,74,0,'8'),(4174,57,3,75,0,'3'),(4175,57,3,77,0,'a:9:{s:8:\"FileName\";s:36:\"a75fbe328361383ac45ba73cdfa4f4fb.j