g ethnic group shows her tattooed face in Drung-Nu Autonomous County of Gongshan, southwest China\'s Yunnan Province, Nov. 27, 2007. The women of the Derung ethnic group used to have their faces tattooed when they turned 12 or 13 as a sign of maturity. The custom began hundreds of years ago. The Dulong people were often attacked by other ethnic groups and women were taken as slaves. To avoid being raped, the Dulong women had their faces tattooed to make themselves less attractive. However, the old custom began disappearing after the founding of the People\'s Republic of China and today tattooed women faces can only be seen among some aged people of the group.\"'),(6386,107,2,38,0,'<kml xmlns=\"http://earth.google.com/kml/2.0\"><Folder><name>OpenLayers export</name><description>Exported on Wed Nov 14 2012 10:30:06 GMT-0800 (PST)</description></Folder></kml>||||osm\r\nAsia'),(9926,108,2,6,1,'<a href=\"http://www.orkneyjar.com/history/picts\">Who were the Picts?</a>'),(9925,108,2,38,0,'<kml xmlns=\"http://earth.google.com/kml/2.0\"><Folder><name>OpenLayers export</name><description>Exported on Wed Nov 28 2012 16:38:54 GMT-0800 (PST)</description><Placemark><name>OpenLayers.Feature.Vector_158</name><description>No description available</description><Point><coordinates>-225030.61124028,7255950.5770176</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder></kml>|4|655523.95448242|6663042.8806349|ghyb\r\nEurope'),(9923,108,2,40,0,'2000'),(9922,108,2,45,0,'Sigrud Towrie'),(9921,108,2,48,0,'Orkneyjar'),(9920,108,2,39,0,'Sigurd Towrie'),(9919,108,2,41,0,'An overview of who the Picts were and the history of their time in Scotland.'),(6416,80,3,74,0,'8'),(6417,80,3,73,0,'348'),(6418,80,3,72,0,'215'),(8128,109,2,38,0,'<kml xmlns=\"http://earth.google.com/kml/2.0\"><Folder><name>OpenLayers export</name><description>Exported on Wed Nov 28 2012 16:38:06 GMT-0800 (PST)</description><Placemark><name>OpenLayers.Feature.Vector_158</name><description>No description available</description><Point><co