ury - Cultural'),(6935,118,2,41,1,'<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/Ef8E_Tlo82Y\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"420\" height=\"315\"></iframe><br /> Renewed interest in Maori culture has encouraged a resurgence in traditional Maori tattoos. <br /> \"The tattoos or \'mokos\' originate back to pre-colonial times when they detailed ancestry lines and tribal affiliations. \'It\'s the art of kings,\' states moko artist Inya Taylor. To take the pain of the moko is a defining moment in a young warrior\'s life. As one Maori explains: \'If it doesn\'t look really painful every moron\'s going to want one.\'\"'),(6936,118,2,39,0,'Journeyman Pictures'),(7759,119,2,39,0,'Unknown'),(7760,119,2,48,0,'http://iamjericho.hubpages.com/hub/Japanese-Tattoo-Culture'),(7761,119,2,40,0,'Unknown'),(7762,119,2,51,0,'Website'),(7763,119,2,38,0,'<kml xmlns=\"http://earth.google.com/kml/2.0\"><Folder><name>OpenLayers export</name><description>Exported on Mon Nov 26 2012 10:33:44 GMT-0800 (PST)</description><Placemark><name>OpenLayers.Feature.Vector_436</name><description>No description available</description><Point><coordinates>15615167.632147875,4598631.6209961</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder></kml>|1|1290823.1490137|4832196.9041745|ghyb\r\nAsia'),(6931,96,3,73,0,'316'),(6932,96,3,72,0,'419'),(6941,97,3,74,0,'8'),(6942,97,3,73,0,'320'),(6943,97,3,72,0,'430'),(11461,120,2,50,0,'\"Zane from Zealand Tattoo Creating a Unique Maori Tattoo Design\"'),(11462,120,2,49,0,'New Zealand - 21st Century - Cultural'),(11463,120,2,41,1,'<p><iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/2Lv34B1joFU\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\"></iframe><br /> Maori Tattoo design is a process unique to each person. Through understanding the persons journey, family and ambitions in life Zane and the Zealand tattoo team create a unique maori tattoo design. <br /> Backed by traditional maori song with text explanations watch the process from start to finish.</p>\r\n<p>Although the video does not show the traditonal application of Maori tattoo, the process of design and song are accurate to the proper Maori traditions</p>'),(11467,120,2,51,0,'Video'),(11468,120,2,38,0,'<kml xmlns=\"http://earth.google.com/kml/2.0\"><Folder><name>OpenLayers export</name><description>Exported on Fri Nov 16 2012 00:26:59 GMT-0800 (PST)</description></Folder></kml>|4|19164945.580119|-5004155.3469778|ghyb\r\n'),(11464,120,2,39,0,'Zealand Tattoo'),(11465,120,2,45,0,'Phil Benoit'),(11466,120,2,40,0,'2010'),(9350,121,2,6,0,'http://www.pbs.org/skinstories/index.html'),(9345,121,2,39,0,'Public Broadcasting Service'),(9346,121,2,45,0,'pbs.org'),(9347,121,2,47,0,'Pacific Islanders in Communications'),(9348,121,2,51,0,'Website'),(9349,121,2,38,0,'<kml xmlns=\"http://earth.google.com/kml/2.0\"><Folder><name>OpenLayers export</name><description>Exported on Fri Nov 16 2012 00:40:22 GMT-0800 (PST)</description></Folder></kml>|3|-18151000.127283|-4241008.0566848|ghyb\r\n'),(9343,121,2,49,0,'New Zealand & Samoa - 21st Century - Cultural'),(9344,121,2,41,0,'\"Skin Stories is an anthology of stories and stunning images gathered from the hot spots of Pacific tattoo: from the steaming landscape of Rotorua in New Zealand to the vibrant gathering of the first international tattoo convention in Apia, Samoa; from the terraced, lush taro fields of Maui to the golden beaches of O’ahu and California.\"'),(9342,121,2,50,0,'\"Skin Stories: The Art and Culture of Polynesian Tattoo\"'),(7764,119,2,6,1,'<a href=\"http://iamjericho.hubpages.com/hub/Japanese-Tattoo-Culture\">\"Japanese Tattoo Culture\"</a>'),(7758,119,2,41,0,'This webpage provides much of the background information about when and why tattoos were popular in Japan. '),(7799,27,2,6,1,'<a href=\"http://tattootemple.hk/history-of-tattooing\">\"Tattoo Temple\"</a>'),(7790,27,2,50,0,'\"Tattoo Temple\"'),(7709,41,2,45,0,'gbtimes'),(7704,41,2,50,0,'\"Skin Deep - The art of tattooing in China\"'),(10435,42,2,48,0,'http://www.buzzle.com/articles/history-of-tattoos.html'),(10433,42,2,41,0,'\"Tattoos are one of the oldest symbols used in various ancient tribes, and yes, they played a significant role, even in those days. Read this article on history of tattoos and find out all the thinking and ideologies that existed back then, when this body art form was originated...\"'),(10436,42,2,45,0,'Buzzle'),(10434,42,2,39,0,'Shalu Bhatti'),(7867,45,2,50,0,'\"Tattoo World\"'),(7868,45,2,49,0,'Asia, 21st Century, Historical'),(7869,45,2,41,0,'\"This paper is a holistic look at the world of tattoo. It covers the history of the practice in three major world regions, Europe, Asia and the Pacific, from the earliest known references to tattooing to modern day tattoo culture that spans the globe. It also provides a discussion of some of the major issues that surround the practice, including such topics as tattooing in relation to the body, authenticity, commodification and meaning, functions, medical and legal concerns and the impact of technological developments on the practice, and the increase in popularity of tattooing in recent decades.\"'),(9524,173,3,77,0,'a:8:{s:8:\"FileName\";s:36:\"e6826c1a0491d3d234418a91d3278db3.jpg\";s:12:\"FileDateTime\";i:1354237900;s:8:\"FileSize\";i:80212;s:8:\"FileType\";i:2;s:8:\"MimeType\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";s:13:\"SectionsFound\";s:7:\"COMMENT\";s:8:\"COMPUTED\";a:4:{s:4:\"html\";s:24:\"width=\"495\" height=\"550\"\";s:6:\"Height\";i:550;s:5:\"Width\";i:495;s:7:\"IsColor\";i:1;}s:7:\"COMMENT\";a:1:{i:0;s:57:\"CREATOR: gd-jpeg v1.0 (using IJG JPEG v62), quality = 90\n\";}}'),(7890,46,2,6,1,'<a href=\"http://www.crystalinks.com/tattoo.html\">\"Tattoo\"</a>'),(7884,46,2,41,0,'\"Tattooing is one of the oldest art forms on the planet, dating to prehistoric times and cave dwellers who often created tattoos as part of ritual practices linked to shamanism, protection, connection with their gods, and embuing them with magica powers. Early tattooing was used to symbolize the fertility of the earth and of wo